&lt;p&gt;Since the early days of the Internet, I have built several blogs from scratch or using   blog technology du jour. This blog is built using &lt;a href=&quot;https://fastpages.fast.ai&quot;&gt;fastpages&lt;/a&gt;, which is a part of  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fast.ai/&quot;&gt;fast.ai&lt;/a&gt;â€™s tool kit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This diagram illustrates a process for creating  fastpages posts&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/techtalkJohnBlog/images/fastpagesdev.png&quot; width=&quot;480&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
    &lt;em&gt;Creating Fastpages Posts&lt;/em&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;fastpages-posts&quot;&gt;Fastpages Posts&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://fastpages.fast.ai/fastpages/jupyter/2020/02/21/introducing-fastpages.html&quot;&gt;Fastpages&lt;/a&gt; supports creating blog post using &lt;a href=&quot;https://jupyter.org/&quot;&gt;Jupyter Notebooks&lt;/a&gt;,  &lt;a href=&quot;https://guides.github.com/features/mastering-markdown/&quot;&gt;Markdown&lt;/a&gt;, and Microsoft Word.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;github-pages&quot;&gt;GitHub Pages&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fastpages uses  &lt;a href=&quot;https://pages.github.com&quot;&gt;GitHuB Pages&lt;/a&gt;, and a cast of creative APIs, and apps to compile and deploy blog.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;editing&quot;&gt;Editing&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My go to editor is &lt;a href=&quot;https://code.visualstudio.com&quot;&gt;VScode&lt;/a&gt;  with the &lt;a href=&quot;https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=bierner.github-markdown-preview&quot;&gt;Github Markdown Preview&lt;/a&gt; extension pack. A nice feature is  GitHub markdown preview.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fastpages uses &lt;a href=&quot;https://pages.github.com&quot;&gt;GitHub Pages&lt;/a&gt; for creating blog posts which uses &lt;a href=&quot;https://guides.github.com/features/mastering-markdown/&quot;&gt;GitHub Markdown&lt;/a&gt;. It  has some features  other markdown dialects may not have, like commenting out lines of markdown and embedding html&lt;/p&gt;

